From 12241c4d059306c0d0dcb45e76690de1db63036b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Yvette Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 22:49:37 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 158/174] mm: PGCL: scale total_swap_pages to MMUPAGE in
 overcommit accounting

vm_commit_limit() and __vm_enough_memory()'s OVERCOMMIT_GUESS check build
their limit in MMUPAGE units -- totalram_pages() << PAGE_MMUSHIFT,
sysctl_overcommit_kbytes >> (MMUPAGE_SHIFT - 10), and the request `pages`
is MMUPAGE-granular -- but added total_swap_pages raw.  total_swap_pages
counts swap slots, which under PGCL are PAGE (cluster) sized, so swap was
under-counted by PAGE_MMUCOUNT (16x at PGCL=4, 64x at PGCL=6): e.g. the
laptop's 80G of swap would be treated as 5G (pgcl4) / 1.25G (pgcl6) of
overcommit headroom, spuriously denying mmap/brk under OVERCOMMIT_GUESS
and lowering the OVERCOMMIT_NEVER limit.

Scale total_swap_pages by << PAGE_MMUSHIFT at both sites.  Identity at
PAGE_MMUSHIFT == 0.  Compile-verified mm/util.o at PGCL=6.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 mm/util.c | 10 ++++++++--
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mm/util.c b/mm/util.c
index 0cd11e262d32..d03ed9e1b539 100644
--- a/mm/util.c
+++ b/mm/util.c
@@ -911,7 +911,12 @@ unsigned long vm_commit_limit(void)
 		allowed = (((totalram_pages() - hugetlb_total_pages())
 			    << PAGE_MMUSHIFT)
 			   * sysctl_overcommit_ratio / 100);
-	allowed += total_swap_pages;
+	/*
+	 * total_swap_pages counts swap slots, which are PAGE (cluster) sized;
+	 * the rest of this limit is in MMUPAGE units, so scale swap up too.
+	 * Identity at PAGE_MMUSHIFT == 0.
+	 */
+	allowed += total_swap_pages << PAGE_MMUSHIFT;
 
 	return allowed;
 }
@@ -971,7 +976,8 @@ int __vm_enough_memory(const struct mm_struct *mm, long pages, int cap_sys_admin
 		return 0;
 
 	if (sysctl_overcommit_memory == OVERCOMMIT_GUESS) {
-		if (pages > (totalram_pages() << PAGE_MMUSHIFT) + total_swap_pages)
+		if (pages > (totalram_pages() << PAGE_MMUSHIFT) +
+			    (total_swap_pages << PAGE_MMUSHIFT))
 			goto error;
 		return 0;
 	}
